cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new index structure for efficient pattern search and random access on similar strings with gaps. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the space and time complexity of the proposed index. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper mentions the functionalities of pattern search and random access, which are important in information retrieval. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper proposes an index structure for efficient search on genomic data, which is often stored in databases. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves the design of a new version of the suffix array using alignment transformation and a new definition of the alignment-suffix, which may involve discrete mathematics concepts.
